comments.message:
The way I've dealt with flexible array members in libpldm is as follows:

In the `.h`:

```
struct foo {
   size_t len;
#ifndef __cplusplus
   unsigned char data[] __attribute__((counted_by(len)));
#endif
};

void *foo_data(struct foo *foo);
```

In the `.c`:

```
void *foo_data(struct foo *foo)
{
    return foo->data;
}
```

This way the access to the flexible array member is constrained to C, but the member is accessible in C++ via the accessor function.

With respect to the struct definition, flexible array members have zero size, so `sizeof(struct foo)` is the same in both C and C++ despite the ifdef:

https://godbolt.org/z/93jqTde8K
